    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000045/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - Adrift in an alcohol induced oblivion, the faculties of your mind speak to you.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000045/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING / DREAM1
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000281/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - The ceiling fan is spinning like the blades of some rickety old airship about to fall on you. A truly horrendous neck-tie has somehow attached itself to one of the blades.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000281/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING / CEILING FAN
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x010000040000032B/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - A mirror hangs on the bathroom wall, above a bent and broken sink.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x010000040000032B/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING / BATHROOM MIRROR
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000561/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - A striking young woman in a silver body-suit smokes in the hostel hallway. She addresses you as if you were a police officer. You may use your finger pistols for a SUGGESTION red-check. Failure gives you some forewarning about what's going on.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000561/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING F2 / KLAASJE 1
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x010000040000059A/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - Downstairs ltn Kim Kitsuragi - precinct 57th's finest - is waiting to solve THE HANGED MAN with you as an inter-district co-op. It would appear Precinct 41 sent you to investigate the lynching of a "Whitewater mercenary" in "Martinaise". And that you are indeed a police officer. Kim briefs you on the case and your relationship begins - likely on the wrong foot, but not necessarily.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x010000040000059A/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING / KIM INTRO
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x01000004000005AF/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - ltn Kitsuragi suggests you talk to the manager of the Whirling-In-Rags first. Garte is a hub of knowledge on the area and the case and you will come back to him later. He is also a problem, asking you to pay for the night, to pay for "the damages". It does not reflect well on you.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x01000004000005AF/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING F1 / GARTE
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000618/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - Un cadavre est pendu au pin. Il s’agit d’un homme d’âge moyen, portant des bottes d’armure blanche ainsi qu’un slip blanc serré. A medium PERCEPTION white-check lets you find a bullet hole in the back of his mouth, a low LOGIC white check that he was killed before hanging. A low THOUGHT CABINET w-c sees that the bullet is antique.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000618/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - YARD / HANGED MAN
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000653/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - An easy PERCEPTION check highlights a scattering of bullet holes in the wall. Pass a medium VISUAL CALCULUS and the interact appears as a ghostly mass execution perpetrated by dotted lines against a row of figures facing the wall. Either way, dialogue with the object has you and Lt Kitsuragi figure out it was an execution after the amphibious assault. You may relive it as an INLAND EMPIRE dream sequence later.
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x0100000400000653/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WESTCOAST / EXECUTIONS VISCAL
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x01000004000006C5/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - "Meeting Klaasje again, on the roof\n 0) Intro\n 1) Your name and \n 2) why u here? (orbs and drugs from room) \n 3) Wildflower\n 5) did you hear me night before / last time we saw\n 6) Looking for Ruby"
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x01000004000006C5/Title
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - WHIRLING F3 / KLAASJE MAIN
      Flags: 00
      Languages_Touch: []
    - Term: Conversation/0x01000004000006E7/Description
      TermType: 0
      Languages:
      - The Washing Woman who gives you access to the alternate sleeping location -- the shack. Includes fishing village mood and Evrart quest stuff.
